 We were fortunate that one of our Rangers from the Glade picked up on the putrid sent of a Necromancer before he was able to cast his evil upon us.  We quickly engaged the Darkelves.  We had them beaten long before the battle had begun.  We were a large party of mixed classes.  This surprise attack was ill supported, and undermanned.  But they did manage to cover an assassin well enough to get past me.  I heard a scream to my rear &quot;GAVIN!!!!&quot;….I turned to see Arianna was being faced with a short Darkeelf woman attempting to slash her with a wicked looking dagger.  Arianna dodged the blue woman's attempts, and bashed her once with her staff, but it was clear that if she did not get help, this fight would not last.     I charged the woman, but she rolled into me, and attempted to get behind me.  I spun on her, and was about to bring down my great sword on her when the woman shimmied, and disappeared.  Arianna cast a spell of seeing on the party, but it was confirmed that the Darkelves had ported away.  We suffered only one injured to their 5 losses.  <br>
  A mixed Company of Elves relieved us shortly after this last engagement.  The Commander of the combined force informed us that the Orcs had retreated into their strong hold of Crushbone, and we were to head to Kaladim for payment.  We were not prepared for the opulent reception we were to receive.  It seemed that our party's exploits had become the talk of the campaign.  Between the blood vengeance of the Halas mercenaries, and the crusade led by Arianna's party, we had defeated almost all of the Dark Elven supporters of the Crushbone offensive.  Arianna, and I stayed in Kaladim for the week, and the started back to Qeynos.  The trip back was a bit different then the one that had brought us to the magic Isle of the Fey.  Instead of the long, and dangerous trek across the Antonican continent. All we had to do was make a half day's ride into GreaterFey to the Wizard's spires.  There we met with the Wizard's Guild leader of Qeynos (Arianna's Father), and to my great surprise my parents.  It seemed that there was a surprise in store for me, and there was no way that either Arianna, her parents, or mine were going to leave things to chance.  <br>
&quot;Looks to me that what ever chance you had of escaping brother, is now gone.  She's Got ya&quot; Angus MacTavish said as the air around us began to crackle.  Arianna gave my friend a withering look, but he only beamed a smile at her.  He finished his sentence on the Western plains of Karana, which caused him to hesitate a bit.  Looking around with a look of confusion on his face he said &quot;I am only watching over my brother young lass.  After all he, and I have completed a long quest. It pains me to see him now brought to the alter without so much as a good Halas beating&quot; He finished with an impish grin.  <br>
&quot;Who said anything about an Alter?&quot; Arianna replied with a cat caught with a paw in the birdcage look on her face. <br>
&quot;That will be enough my children.&quot; My mother cut in.  &quot;We still have several hours of travel before us before we reach the city, so stand still while I invoke the spirits of our kinsfolk of the forest to speed us on our way&quot;  My mother cast several spells along with my father and then we were off to the city of Qeynos running with all speed, and stamina of wolves.  I held to the rear of this group of friends as we ran along the Karana river.  I looked at the faces of each of my family and companions and suddenly realized that we were indeed wolves.  No not the true four legged sort, but we were a pack.  We were devoted to each other.  Our lives were intertwined, and depended on each member of the pack.  Wolves we were indeed, and like wolves we would triumph over our enemy's through each other.  I was comforted, and contented by this.  It must have shown on my face too, because Angus trotting at my side broke my mussing with a playful shove.  &quot;Hah, if I didn't know you better Gavin, I would swear that your looking forward to getting married.  I guess I will have to have our kinsmen give ya a good ole fashion Halas send off once we get to Qeynos.&quot;  I looked at my friend in surprise.  &quot;Who's getting married?  I am not getting married yet!&quot;  I replied.  &quot;I have to much to do before I settle down to marriage.&quot;  I replied.  &quot;You better look around you, you stupid Barbarian&quot; This time the voice was Shalia's.  &quot;What do you think the top brass of the Qeynos Wizard's Guild, and the 2 most respected Shaman in Norath have made a special trip to get your party for? Your not that special Gavin&quot; She had a catch in her voice after that last sentence, and I could tell that Shalia wanted to be here with us.  I was afraid to answer, so I remained silent.  She knew I missed her though.  <br>
  It wasn't long before we were in Qeynos hills, and on the road to Qeynos.  Once near the gates I could see that banners of welcome had been hung from the walls of the city, and there were crowds of people awaiting our triumphant return.  Arianna drew close to me, and whispered &quot;Is she jealous Gavin?&quot;  I looked at Arianna in surprise, and asked &quot; Is who jealous?&quot;  &quot;Shalia of course you lout.  Who else would I be talking about.  She's been staring at me from your shoulders since my father teleported us from Greaterfeydark.&quot;  I stopped in my tracks, and turned to Angus who was with the mercenary escort that had started the trek from Qeynos with me the year before.  &quot;Do you see her brother?&quot; I asked him.  &quot; See who Gavin?&quot;  he replied with baffled look.  &quot;Only you, and Arianna can see me Gavin, I wanted her to see me so that she would know that I am still with you, and tell her that I am happy for you both.&quot; <br>
&quot;She says that she is only happy for us, and that she wanted you to know that she is still with me.&quot; <br>
&quot;I will take good care of him Shalia, and you are welcome in our family.&quot; Arianna said looking at a place just over my head.<br>
  The throng of people had to be held back by the Qeynos Guards as our party approached the gates.  Before the gate of Qeynos stood two figures.  One was Antonious Bale, and the other was none other the High Chief of the North.  My father Gerhard Macalister, and my Mother Reanen flanked by Bastin Q'Tonoth faced me.  &quot;Gavin, as the leader of our party it is your duty to announce the arrival, and proclaim our deeds to the tribe.  Now kneel son, and receive the blessing of the Six Hammers, and that of Radcet Nife.&quot;  Our Party stood in a half circle facing the Qeynos, and Halas dignitaries as I received the blessings from my parents, and from Bastin, Arianna's father.  Once finished I stood before them.  &quot;Now select a guard, and stand before our leaders, and present our deeds Gavin.  Proclaim to all that on this day our 2 cities of Qeynos, and Halas are one, and have helped to save our distant allies, and cousins on the Isle of the Fey.&quot;  My mother could get ceremonial at times, but I knew what she said asked of me was part of an ancient Halas tradition.  I selected Angus, Arianna, and the ghost of Shalia, and then turned to the City gates, and made my proclamation of victory to the people of the West.  <br>
&quot;People of the West.  I stand before you as your brother, and ask that you welcome my party back to the Village.  We have quested long, and far to bring you news of Triumph over evil, and of justice.  My brothers, and sisters whom you see behind me have assured the freedom of our Cities.  Will you welcome them?!&quot; <br>
  The crowd roared it's welcome.  Shalia was beaming at me from my side, and noticed that she was no longer ethereal, but substantial.  She was dressed in white robes, and her hair was touched with gray.  But she was there.  I lifted her up, and kissed her soundly, and helped her to her usual place on my shoulders, and then turned to reach out for Arianna, and the rest of my party.   I noticed that the dwarven woman who was so brutally wounded in the forest of Feydark walked now whole, and alongside Angus.  There were others walking with our party as the Tribunal allowed those that had been avenged to return to earth to help in celebration one last time.<br>
  Antonious Bale motioned for silence, and stepped forward to greet us.  He took my hand, and asked me to kneel once again.  &quot;My Brothers from the North told me that a Brave, and Powerful party of brothers, and sister were arriving from the war in Greaterfeydark.  My Brother the High Chief of Halas has honored us with his presence, and allowed us to present the honors, and rewards of the gratitude of our people here in the city of Qeynos.  Before me is the man known as Gavin of the clan Macalister.  Who from this day forth shall be known as the Wolfguard of the North.&quot;  The High Chief then stepped forward, and presented to me one of the most sought after swords in all of Norath.  The Langseax of the Wolves.  &quot;Go forth Gavin of the Clan Macalister.  Bring Pride on your Name, and to that of the Wolves of the North.&quot;  The High Chief then stood to the side, as Antonious beckoned to Arianna.  She also knelt at my side, and before the rulers of Qeynos, and of Halas. <br>
 &quot;People of the West. Know ye that from this day forth these two souls before me will be known as one.  They will travel as one always, and they will walk in the after world as one.&quot; <br>
 I was shocked, and looked from Shalia to Arianna to Angus.  All of them looked at me as if I was a child.  I had no Idea what was going on, until Antonious started the Marriage rights.  But I have to say that even now I look on that day as the best day of my life. <br>
&quot;Wolfguard, do you take this woman of Radcet Nife to your home of free will, and do you swear to protect, and provide for her until which day are called to our gods?&quot;  I looked at Arianna, and I knew that this was meant to be.  At that moment I knew that my vow was not only mine to her, but the Tribunal's, to Radcet Nife.  I would not know until much later what this meant, but for now all I could do was speak my heart.<br>
&quot;I swear with my last breath that I will protect, and provide for Arianna until the Tribunal calls me home.&quot;<br>
&quot;Arianna, do you swear to walk at the side of the Wolfguard, and to honor, and protect his children until which time that the Healer should call you home?&quot;<br>
Arianna simply looked into my eyes, and whispered. &quot;Yes&quot;<br>
